    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq" id="docs">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span class="gradient-text">Questions</span></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-grid">
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>What is Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC)?</summary>
                    <p>Post-Quantum Cryptography refers to cryptographic algorithms that are secure against attacks by both classical and quantum computers. Our platform uses ML-KEM and ML-DSA, which are standardized by NIST in FIPS 203 and FIPS 204.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Do I need my own quantum hardware access?</summary>
                    <p>No! We provide access to IBM Quantum, AWS Braket, Azure Quantum, and D-Wave through our platform. You can also use our local simulator for development and testing at no cost.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>What optimization problems can I solve?</summary>
                    <p>You can solve any QUBO (Quadratic Unconstrained Binary Optimization) problem, including Max-Cut, TSP, Graph Coloring, Portfolio Optimization, and custom combinatorial problems.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>How does the free tier work?</summary>
                    <p>The free tier gives you 100 optimization jobs per month using our local simulator. It's perfect for learning, prototyping, and small experiments. Upgrade anytime to access real quantum hardware.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Is my data encrypted?</summary>
                    <p>Yes! All data is encrypted using AES-256-GCM with keys exchanged via ML-KEM-768. Digital signatures use ML-DSA-65. This hybrid approach provides quantum-safe security for all your optimization data.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Can I deploy on-premise?</summary>
                    <p>Yes, enterprise customers can deploy QuantumSafe Optimize on their own infrastructure. We provide Docker containers and Terraform configurations for Azure deployment.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

